Setting Up CoinGecko API Key with Google Colab Secrets¶

This tutorial uses Google Colab, a free cloud service that allows you to write and execute Python in your browser with zero configuration required, access to free GPUs, and easy sharing. Using Google Colab eliminates the need for local setup and ensures that everyone has access to the same computing environment, making it easier to follow along and troubleshoot.

Google Colab¶

Make sure that Google Colaboratory is added to your Google Drive account's connected apps as you see below. In your Google Drive account, click on '+New' > 'More'. If you do not see Google Colaboratory in the menu, click on '+Connect more apps'.

Search for "Google Colaboratory", and install it.

CoinGecko API Key¶

You will need an API key from CoinGecko to fetch cryptocurrency market data. Sign up for a free API key at CoinGecko API. Once you have your API key, you'll need to store it securely in your Google Colab environment.

Google Colab Secrets¶

To securely manage your CoinGecko API key within Google Colab, follow these steps:

  1. Click the key icon in the left side menu.

  1. Click on + Add new secret.

  1. Enter the name as "coingecko_key", paste your CoinGecko API key as the value, and grant notebook access.

Finally, retrieve your API key from Google Colab Secrets.

In [ ]:
from google.colab import userdata
coingecko_key = userdata.get('coingecko_key')
